The Garden Prayer Committee says it will pray for the nation and justice in the wake of what it calls 'the recent evil in government'. JOHANNESBURG - Hundreds of people from different religious denominations have gathered at the Union Buildings to pray for South Africa's government. The gathering is an initiative by the Garden Prayer Committee. The committee says it will pray for the nation and for righteousness and justice in the wake of what it calls “the recent evil in government”. The committee’s Pastor Frank Booysen said: “The purpose of our prayer is for the nation and for our government because of the evils that are being revealed and reflected in them.”  